criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Persons with a history of brain injury (e.g., Traumatic Brain Injury; TBI) or acquired
             BI such as stroke, hypoxia, ruptured aneurysm, or metabolic encephalopathy);

          -  18 years of age and older;

          -  at least six months post-injury; and

          -  able to speak English fluently.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  at imminent risk of psychiatric breakdown, or in imminent danger of hurting themselves
             or others;

          -  active psychosis;

          -  aphasia that limits group participation;

          -  significant neurobehavioral difficulties that would be deemed disruptive to group
             participation.
